toredIQ product library</linktext><?ditaot genshortdesc?><shortdesc class="- map/shortdesc "></shortdesc></topicmeta></topic><topic href="Topics/Concept/contacting_ibm_storediq_customer_support.html" data-id="contacting_ibm_storediq_customer_support" wh-toc-id="contacting_ibm_storediq_customer_support-d62e76"><title>Contacting IBM StoredIQ customer support</title><shortdesc><p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" class="shortdesc"></p></shortdesc><topicmeta><resourceid class="- topic/resourceid " oxy-source="topic" appid="contacting_ibm_storediq_customer_support"></resourceid><navtitle class="- topic/navtitle ">Contacting IBM StoredIQ customer support</navtitle><?ditaot gentext?><linktext class="- map/linktext ">Contacting IBM StoredIQ customer support</linktext><?ditaot genshortdesc?><shortdesc class="- map/shortdesc "></shortdesc></topicmeta></topic></topic><topic href="Topics/Reference/ibm_storediq_components.html" data-id="ibm_storediq_components" wh-toc-id="ibm_storediq_components-d62e98"><title>IBM StoredIQ components</title><shortdesc><p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" class="shortdesc">The IBM StoredIQ solution consists of these components: the application stack, the gateway, the data         server, and optionally the Elasticsearch cluster.</p></shortdesc><topicmeta><resourceid class="- topic/resourceid " oxy-source="topic" appid="ibm_storediq_components"></resourceid><navtitle class="- topic/navtitle ">IBM StoredIQ components</navtitle><?ditaot gentext?><linktext class="- map/linktext ">IBM StoredIQ components</linktext><?ditaot genshortdesc?><shortdesc class="- map/shortdesc ">The IBM StoredIQ solution consists of these components: the application stack, the gateway, the data         server, and optionally the Elasticsearch cluster.</shortdesc></topicmeta><topic href="Topics/Concept/solution_components.html" data-id="solution_components" wh-toc-id="solution_components-d62e109"><title>Solution Components</title><shortdesc><p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" class="shortdesc">IBM StoredIQ provides three solution components: the gateway, data servers, and application stack         (AppStack).</p></shortdesc><topicmeta><resourceid class="- topic/resourceid " oxy-source="topic" appid="solution_components"></resourceid><navtitle class="- topic/navtitle ">Solution Components</navtitle><?ditaot gentext?><linktext class="- map/linktext ">Solution Components</linktext><?ditaot genshortdesc?><shortdesc class="- map/shortdesc ">IBM StoredIQ provides three solution components: the gateway, data servers, and application stack         (AppStack).</shortdesc></topicmeta></topic><topic href="Topics/Concept/applications_of_ibm_storediq.html" data-id="applications_of_ibm_storediq" wh-toc-id="applications_of_ibm_storediq-d62e120"><title>Applications of IBM StoredIQ</title><shortdesc><p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" class="shortdesc">IBM StoredIQ provides interface applications that help fulfill its solution goals.</p></shortdesc><topicmeta><resourceid class="- topic/resourceid " oxy-source="topic" appid="applications_of_ibm_storediq"></resourceid><navtitle class="- topic/navtitle ">Applications of IBM StoredIQ</navtitle><?ditaot gentext?><linktext class="- map/linktext ">Applications of IBM StoredIQ</linktext><?ditaot genshortdesc?><shortdesc class="- map/shortdesc ">IBM StoredIQ provides interface applications that help fulfill its solution goals.</shortdesc></topicmeta></topic></topic><topic href="Topics/Task/planning_for_deployment.html" data-id="planning_for_deployment1" wh-toc-id="planning_for_deployment1-d62e132"><title>Planning for deployment</title><shortdesc><p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" class="shortdesc"></p></shortdesc><topicmeta><resourceid class="- topic/resourceid " oxy-source="topic" appid="planning_for_deployment1"></resourceid><navtitle class="- topic/navtitle ">Planning for deployment</navtitle><?ditaot gentext?><linktext class="- map/linktext ">Planning for deployment</linktext><?ditaot genshortdesc?><shortdesc class="- map/shortdesc "></shortdesc></topicmeta><topic href="Topics/Reference/open_virtual_appliance__ova__configuration_requirements.html" data-id="open_virtual_appliance__ova__configuration_requirements" wh-toc-id="open_virtual_appliance__ova__configuration_requirements-d62e142"><title>Open Virtual Appliance (OVA) configuration requirements</title><shortdesc><p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" class="shortdesc">IBM StoredIQ is deployed as virtual appliances and is supported in VMware ESXi 5.0 (all fix pack levels) or         VMware ESXi 6.0 (all fix pack levels) environments. You must have a virtual infrastructure that meets the         IBM StoredIQ hardware requirements.</p></shortdesc><topicmeta><resourceid class="- topic/resourceid " oxy-source="topic" appid="open_virtual_appliance__ova__configuration_requirements"></resourceid><navtitle class="- topic/navtitle ">Open Virtual Appliance (OVA) configuration requirements</navtitle><?ditaot gentext?><linktext class="- map/linktext ">Open Virtual Appliance (OVA) configuration requirements</linktext><?ditaot genshortdesc?><shortdesc class="- map/shortdesc ">IBM StoredIQ is deployed as virtual appliances and is supported in VMware ESXi 5.0 (all fix pack levels) or         VMware ESXi 6.0 (all fix pack levels) environments. You must have a virtual infrastructure that meets the         IBM StoredIQ hardware requirements.</shortdesc></topicmeta></topic><topic href="Topics/Reference/network_and_port_requirements.html" data-id="network_and_port_requirements" wh-toc-id="network_and_port_requirements-d62e169"><title>Network and port requirements</title><shortdesc><p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" class="shortdesc"></p></shortdesc><topicmeta><resourceid class="- topic/resourceid " oxy-source="topic" appid="network_and_port_requirements"></resourceid><navtitle class="- topic/navtitle ">Network and port requirements</navtitle><?ditaot gentext?><linktext class="- map/linktext ">Network and port requirements</linktext><?ditaot genshortdesc?><shortdesc class="- map/shortdesc "></shortdesc></topicmeta></topic><topic href="Topics/Concept/environment_sizing_guidelines.html" data-id="environment_sizing_guidelines" wh-toc-id="environment_sizing_guidelines-d62e200"><title>Environment sizing guidelines</title><shortdesc><p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" class="shortdesc">To size an environment precisely, you must understand the factors such as harvest frequency, complexity         of the source, and use case scenarios that drive application use and action execution.</p></shortdesc><topicmeta><resourceid class="- topic/resourceid " oxy-source="topic" appid="environment_sizing_guidelines"></resourceid><navtitle class="- topic/navtitle ">Environment sizing guidelines</navtitle><?ditaot gentext?><linktext class="- map/linktext ">Environment sizing guidelines</linktext><?ditaot genshortdesc?><shortdesc class="- map/shortdesc ">To size an environment precisely, you must understand the factors such as harvest frequency, complexity         of the source, and use case scenarios that drive application use and action execution.</shortdesc></topicmeta></topic><topic href="Topics/Task/stack_provisioning_prerequisites.html" data-id="stack_provisioning_prerequisites" wh-toc-id="stack_provisioning_prerequisites-d62e219"><title>Stack-provisioning prerequisites</title><shortdesc><p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" class="shortdesc">Before a deployment, verify that you meet these prerequisites.</p></shortdesc><topicmeta><resourceid class="- topic/resourceid " oxy-source="topic" appid="stack_provisioning_prerequisites"></resourceid><navtitle class="- topic/navtitle ">Stack-provisioning prerequisites</navtitle><?ditaot gentext?><linktext class="- map/linktext ">Stack-provisioning prerequisites</linktext><?ditaot genshortdesc?><shortdesc class="- map/shortdesc ">Before a deployment, verify that you meet these prerequisites.</shortdesc></topicmeta></topic><topic href="Topics/Concept/license_usage_metrics.html" data-id="license_usage_metrics" wh-toc-id="license_usage_metrics-d62e230"><title>License usage metrics</title><shortdesc><p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" class="shortdesc"></p></shortdesc><topicmeta><resourceid class="- topic/resourceid " oxy-source="topic" appid="license_usage_metrics"></resourceid><navtitle class="- topic/navtitle ">License usage metrics</navtitle><?ditaot gentext?><linktext class="- map/linktext ">License usage metrics</linktext><?ditaot genshortdesc?><shortdesc class="- map/shortdesc "></shortdesc></topicmeta></topic><topic href="Topics/Concept/security.html" data-id="security" wh-toc-id="security-d62e240"><title>Security</title><shortdesc><p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" class="shortdesc">Plan and implement specific security measures to protect the application and the data it manages,         especially when you deploy IBM StoredIQ into sensitive environments.         IBM StoredIQ keeps your data secure through encryption, security hardening, and auditing.</p></shortdesc><topicmeta><resourceid class="- topic/resourceid " oxy-source="topic" appid="security"></resourceid><navtitle class="- topic/navtitle ">Security</navtitle><?ditaot gentext?><linktext class="- map/linktext ">Security</linktext><?ditaot genshortdesc?><shortdesc class="- map/shortdesc ">Plan and implement specific security measures to protect the application and the data it manages,         especially when you deploy IBM StoredIQ into sensitive environments.         IBM StoredIQ keeps your data secure through encryption, security hardening, and auditing.</shortdesc></topicmeta></topic></topic><topic href="Topics/Concept/deploying_ibm_storediq.html" data-id="deploying_ibm_storediq" wh-toc-id="deploying_ibm_storediq-d62e260"><title>Deploying IBM StoredIQ</title><shortdesc><p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" class="shortdesc">IBM StoredIQ is a virtual appliance that you deploy and configure in a VMWare virtual host environment.</p></shortdesc><topicmeta><resourceid class="- topic/resourceid " oxy-source="topic" appid="deploying_ibm_storediq"></resourceid><navtitle class="- topic/navtitle ">Deploying IBM StoredIQ</navtitle><?ditaot gentext?><linktext class="- map/linktext ">Deploying IBM StoredIQ</linktext><?ditaot genshortdesc?><shortdesc class="- map/shortdesc ">IBM StoredIQ is a virtual appliance that you deploy and configure in a VMWare virtual host environment.</shortdesc></topicmeta><topic href="Topics/Task/deploying_the_virtual_appliances.html" data-id="deploying_the_virtual_appliances" wh-toc-id="deploying_the_virtual_appliances-d62e271"><title>Deploying the virtual appliances</title><shortdesc><p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" class="shortdesc">Use VMware vSphere Client to deploy the virtual appliances to an ESX server. Deploy OVAs for the         gateway, the data server, and the application stack, preferably in this order. If an Elasticsearch cluster is         also being deployed, those OVAs must be deployed first.</p></shortdesc><topicmeta><resourceid class="- topic/resourceid " oxy-source="topic" appid="deploying_the_virtual_appliances"></resourceid><navtitle class="- topic/navtitle ">Deploying the virtual appliances</navtitle><?ditaot gentext?><linktext class="- map/linktext ">Deploying the virtual appliances</linktext><?ditaot genshortdesc?><shortdesc class="- map/shortdesc ">Use VMware vSphere Client to deploy the virtual appliances to an ESX server. Deploy OVAs for the         gateway, the data server, and the application stack, preferably in this order. If an Elasticsearch cluster is         also being deployed, those OVAs must be deployed first.</shortdesc></topicmeta></topic><topic href="Topics/Task/deploying_ibm_storediq_on_microsoft_hyper_v.html" data-id="deploying_ibm_storediq_on_microsoft_hyper_v" wh-toc-id="deploying_ibm_storediq_on_microsoft_hyper_v-d62e282"><title>Deploying IBM StoredIQ on Microsoft Hyper-V</title><shortdesc><p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml